The usual Heritrix main class already has the option to take an 
order.xml as a command-line argument. Can you try launching that way, 
and see if it works?

Regarding your alternate approach, if it works on your machine, but not 
others, it must be a packaging problem or other difference between your 
setup and your classmates.

Watch the process output and/or heritrix_out.log for any errors that are 
clues to what&#39;s going wrong or missing.

If the process seems to be active but not doing anything, you can see 
where (if anywhere) key threads are by requesting a Java threads stack 
dump. (Send the process SIGQUIT, and watch its STDERR, or use the 
&#39;jstack&#39; utility provided with Java as the same user, passing the JVM 
process-ID.) This may reveal if your main thread, or others, are stuck 
in unexpected ways.

- Gordon @ IA

